# Seiton Brain

Personal AI second brain: capture (Telegram/API) → classify → Obsidian vault;
retrieve (search, RAG `/ask`, digest `/digest`, REST, MCP).

**Produkt:** Öffentliche Entwicklung (MIT, Portfolio). Geplante kommerzielle
Consumer-Edition — [ADR 0004](docs/adr/0004-commercial-consumer-product.md),
[ADR 0005](docs/adr/0005-repo-and-license-strategy.md). Name from **Seiton** (整頓).

## Flow

```
Telegram / API → Worker: [Whisper if voice] → classify → Postgres → .md in vault
              → optional: /ask, /digest (RAG), webhooks, MCP via REST
Web-UI (localhost): /setup → /dashboard, /ask, /notes, /settings
```

## Stack

FastAPI · PostgreSQL + SQLAlchemy (async) + Alembic · Celery + Redis · OpenAI (LLM + Whisper + Embeddings) · pgvector · Jinja2 · Docker Compose · Obsidian vault

## Structure

- `app/telegram/` — webhook, polling, slash commands
- `app/worker/` — Celery tasks (capture, voice, ask, digest)
- `app/llm/` — provider, embeddings, schemas
- `app/services/` — process_message, answer, digest
- `app/vault/` — reader, writer, index (keyword + semantic search)
- `app/api/v1/` — REST API (capture, ask, digest, search, …)
- `app/setup/` — Setup-Wizard (env checks, `.env` schreiben)
- `app/licensing/` — Offline-Lizenz Ed25519 (E21-1), `docs/licensing.md`
- `app/ui/` — Web-UI: templates, static, dashboard/ask API (`/api/ui/*`)
- `app/webhooks/` — outbound events (note.created, note.indexed, …)
- `examples/mcp/` — MCP server for Cursor/Claude
- `examples/n8n/` — Power-user workflow JSONs (no custom node)
- `prompts/` — versioned LLM prompts

